I have about 90% of my test results back from the other day.  If you want to see what horrific long COVID19 looks like (and that's pretty much officially what two specialists think now - my immunologist and my neuro-immunologist), here it is.  Some of my cytokines are 20x normal, and my immune system is completely messed up. 

What's interesting is my COVID19 IgG antibodies aren't dropping very fast.  They should have a half-life about 58 days - mine are dropping with a half life of 350 days.  The worst offender is the IgG antibody for the nucleocapsid, which only comes from natural infection (not the vaccine).

That likely means I have viral persistence - my body never cleared the spike protein, either in full, or fragments of the spike after my immune system busted it into pieces.  I ran these serial tests through ChatGPT O3, and it agreed that it was the most probably driver of this mess.

So likely next on the list are some anti-virals to see if I can help it out a bit.  #LongCovid  Will talk it all over with my immunologist this week.
